# Cursor Rules — FF&E Builder

Read /AGENTS.md before any change.

This project follows the operating rules, tech stack pins, definition of done, and
commit conventions defined in /AGENTS.md. All four agent context files (AGENTS.md,
CLAUDE.md, .cursorrules, .github/copilot-instructions.md) point here so there is a
single source of truth.

Key reminders:
- Never access Neon DB from client code — all queries go through the /api/* Worker.
- Money is integer cents. See /docs/money.md.
- Never commit automatically; draft a conventional-commits message instead.
- Never run destructive commands without explicit user confirmation.
- After any structural change, update README.md and /docs/ in the same commit.
